(Pmar), cardiac SNA, intestinal SNA, blood gas values during prolonged hypoxia (ventilation with 8% O2 in nitrogen for 30 min) in a vagotomized, anesthetized rabbit [after Iriki et al. (1972)]. The increase in ear temperature indicates a decrease in SNA to the ear, a ®nding con®rmed in their subsequent study
